[
    {
        "text": "What if our universe",
        "start": 0.0,
        "duration": 2.41
    },
    {
        "text": "comes with a self-destruct button",
        "start": 2.43,
        "duration": 1.661
    },
    {
        "text": "to eliminate itself",
        "start": 4.091,
        "duration": 1.003
    },
    {
        "text": "so cleanly and efficiently,",
        "start": 5.094,
        "duration": 1.398
    },
    {
        "text": "that every single physical thing",
        "start": 6.492,
        "duration": 1.852
    },
    {
        "text": "would just stop existing",
        "start": 8.344,
        "duration": 1.455
    },
    {
        "text": "and life would be impossible",
        "start": 9.799,
        "duration": 1.833
    },
    {
        "text": "forever.",
        "start": 11.632,
        "duration": 2.039
    },
    {
        "text": "The ultimate ecological catastrophe -",
        "start": 13.671,
        "duration": 2.773
    },
    {
        "text": "vacuum decay.",
        "start": 16.444,
        "duration": 1.5
    },
    {
        "text": "(Theme music)",
        "start": 17.944,
        "duration": 9.419
    },
    {
        "text": "To explain how our universe",
        "start": 27.363,
        "duration": 1.412
    },
    {
        "text": "could destroy itself,",
        "start": 28.775,
        "duration": 1.067
    },
    {
        "text": "we need to understand two principles:",
        "start": 29.842,
        "duration": 2.232
    },
    {
        "text": "One - energy levels.",
        "start": 32.074,
        "duration": 4.228
    },
    {
        "text": "A core idea in physics is that",
        "start": 36.302,
        "duration": 2.101
    },
    {
        "text": "everything has an energy level.",
        "start": 38.403,
        "duration": 1.831
    },
    {
        "text": "The higher the level,\nthe more energy is in the system",
        "start": 40.234,
        "duration": 3.09
    },
    {
        "text": "Wood, for example, has a high level.",
        "start": 43.344,
        "duration": 1.788
    },
    {
        "text": "It can be burnt, a process that",
        "start": 45.132,
        "duration": 1.682
    },
    {
        "text": "releases the chemical energy \nstored in its molecular bonds",
        "start": 46.814,
        "duration": 2.861
    },
    {
        "text": "and turns it into heat.",
        "start": 49.675,
        "duration": 1.889
    },
    {
        "text": "The ash leftover is at a",
        "start": 51.564,
        "duration": 1.821
    },
    {
        "text": "lower energy level than the wood before.",
        "start": 53.385,
        "duration": 3.319
    },
    {
        "text": "Two - stability.",
        "start": 56.704,
        "duration": 2.23
    },
    {
        "text": "Everything in our universe tries to move",
        "start": 58.934,
        "duration": 2.87
    },
    {
        "text": "towards its ground state,\nin which it's completely stable",
        "start": 61.804,
        "duration": 3.011
    },
    {
        "text": "and has as little energy as possible.",
        "start": 64.815,
        "duration": 2.378
    },
    {
        "text": "For example, a ball on a hill is unstable",
        "start": 67.193,
        "duration": 3.141
    },
    {
        "text": "and has a lot of potential energy.",
        "start": 70.334,
        "duration": 2.357
    },
    {
        "text": "When disturbed,\nit will roll down into the valey",
        "start": 72.691,
        "duration": 2.285
    },
    {
        "text": "and lose its potential energy\nin the process",
        "start": 74.976,
        "duration": 2.767
    },
    {
        "text": "The ball is now\nin its ground state and stable.",
        "start": 77.746,
        "duration": 2.826
    },
    {
        "text": "It will remain like that.",
        "start": 80.572,
        "duration": 1.873
    },
    {
        "text": "Everything in our universe",
        "start": 82.445,
        "duration": 1.808
    },
    {
        "text": "follows these two principles.",
        "start": 84.253,
        "duration": 1.66
    },
    {
        "text": "If something has a lot of energy,",
        "start": 85.913,
        "duration": 2.11
    },
    {
        "text": "it's unstable and wants to get rid of it",
        "start": 88.023,
        "duration": 2.174
    },
    {
        "text": "to become stable",
        "start": 90.197,
        "duration": 0.765
    },
    {
        "text": "and reach its ground state.",
        "start": 90.962,
        "duration": 2.911
    },
    {
        "text": "This is true for every system",
        "start": 93.873,
        "duration": 1.595
    },
    {
        "text": "even in the weird world of",
        "start": 95.468,
        "duration": 1.518
    },
    {
        "text": "quantum mechanics.",
        "start": 96.986,
        "duration": 2.348
    },
    {
        "text": "If our current understanding of physics\nis correct, then the universe",
        "start": 99.334,
        "duration": 3.292
    },
    {
        "text": "gets its properties from quantum fields.",
        "start": 102.646,
        "duration": 2.199
    },
    {
        "text": "We explained them in detail",
        "start": 104.845,
        "duration": 1.621
    },
    {
        "text": "in another video.",
        "start": 106.466,
        "duration": 1.452
    },
    {
        "text": "For this video, imagine them",
        "start": 107.918,
        "duration": 1.306
    },
    {
        "text": "as the rules of the universe.",
        "start": 109.224,
        "duration": 1.682
    },
    {
        "text": "They tell particles how to",
        "start": 110.906,
        "duration": 1.461
    },
    {
        "text": "behave and interact",
        "start": 112.367,
        "duration": 2.907
    },
    {
        "text": "Like everything in the universe,",
        "start": 115.274,
        "duration": 1.519
    },
    {
        "text": "they want to be\nin the lowest energy level possible,",
        "start": 116.793,
        "duration": 2.352
    },
    {
        "text": "which is called a vacuum state.",
        "start": 119.145,
        "duration": 2.363
    },
    {
        "text": "This has nothing to do with",
        "start": 121.508,
        "duration": 1.671
    },
    {
        "text": "vacuum in space.",
        "start": 123.179,
        "duration": 1.277
    },
    {
        "text": "It's just called this way",
        "start": 124.456,
        "duration": 1.342
    },
    {
        "text": "because scientists are bad at\nnaming things",
        "start": 125.798,
        "duration": 4.328
    },
    {
        "text": "We then call the fields reached their",
        "start": 130.126,
        "duration": 1.839
    },
    {
        "text": "vacuum state, except maybe one.",
        "start": 131.965,
        "duration": 2.661
    },
    {
        "text": "It's possible that the Higgs Field",
        "start": 134.626,
        "duration": 2.671
    },
    {
        "text": "is not stable, but metastable, which is",
        "start": 137.297,
        "duration": 2.847
    },
    {
        "text": "a fancy way of saying that it",
        "start": 140.144,
        "duration": 1.592
    },
    {
        "text": "pretends to be stable but really is not.",
        "start": 141.736,
        "duration": 3.021
    },
    {
        "text": "It would be a false vacuum.",
        "start": 144.757,
        "duration": 1.871
    },
    {
        "text": "The Higgs Field is responsible for",
        "start": 146.628,
        "duration": 2.479
    },
    {
        "text": "giving particles their mass,",
        "start": 149.107,
        "duration": 1.571
    },
    {
        "text": "which rules how almost everything",
        "start": 150.678,
        "duration": 1.729
    },
    {
        "text": "in the universe interacts.",
        "start": 152.407,
        "duration": 1.901
    },
    {
        "text": "What would happen if the Higgs Field\nis a false vacuum?",
        "start": 154.308,
        "duration": 3.251
    },
    {
        "text": "Think of our ball in the valley:",
        "start": 157.559,
        "duration": 1.884
    },
    {
        "text": "the ball is the Higgs Field.",
        "start": 159.443,
        "duration": 2.882
    },
    {
        "text": "The valley might not be the\nlowest energy state for the Higgs Field.",
        "start": 162.325,
        "duration": 3.491
    },
    {
        "text": "There might an even deeper valley\nthat it wants to get to.",
        "start": 165.816,
        "duration": 2.971
    },
    {
        "text": "This would mean that the Higgs Field\nhas a lot of potential energy,",
        "start": 168.787,
        "duration": 2.611
    },
    {
        "text": "waiting to be released.",
        "start": 171.398,
        "duration": 1.809
    },
    {
        "text": "The Higgs Field could be\nlike a piece of wood",
        "start": 173.207,
        "duration": 2.718
    },
    {
        "text": "but drenched in gasoline,",
        "start": 175.925,
        "duration": 1.453
    },
    {
        "text": "waiting to set the universe on fire.",
        "start": 177.378,
        "duration": 2.699
    },
    {
        "text": "A random spark like quantum tunneling",
        "start": 180.077,
        "duration": 1.703
    },
    {
        "text": "could release the potential energy",
        "start": 181.78,
        "duration": 2.026
    },
    {
        "text": "of the Higgs Fields.",
        "start": 183.806,
        "duration": 1.441
    },
    {
        "text": "This could happen at any time",
        "start": 185.247,
        "duration": 1.541
    },
    {
        "text": "and without warning.",
        "start": 186.788,
        "duration": 1.5
    },
    {
        "text": "If at any point in space,",
        "start": 188.288,
        "duration": 1.619
    },
    {
        "text": "this so-called vacuum decay starts,",
        "start": 189.907,
        "duration": 2.1
    },
    {
        "text": "there is no turning back.",
        "start": 192.007,
        "duration": 2.068
    },
    {
        "text": "As the Higgs Field crashes into",
        "start": 194.075,
        "duration": 1.884
    },
    {
        "text": "the lower energy state,",
        "start": 195.959,
        "duration": 1.36
    },
    {
        "text": "it releases a massive amount of",
        "start": 197.319,
        "duration": 1.827
    },
    {
        "text": "potential energy.",
        "start": 199.146,
        "duration": 1.474
    },
    {
        "text": "This energy pushes the space around it",
        "start": 200.62,
        "duration": 1.708
    },
    {
        "text": "over the barrier, which releases",
        "start": 202.328,
        "duration": 1.399
    },
    {
        "text": "more potential energy.",
        "start": 203.727,
        "duration": 1.95
    },
    {
        "text": "A sphere of the new stable Higgs Field,",
        "start": 205.677,
        "duration": 2.174
    },
    {
        "text": "or true vacuum, grows at the",
        "start": 207.851,
        "duration": 1.658
    },
    {
        "text": "speed of light in all directions.",
        "start": 209.509,
        "duration": 1.988
    },
    {
        "text": "Imagine it like setting a sea of gasoline,",
        "start": 211.497,
        "duration": 3.604
    },
    {
        "text": "the size of the universe, on fire.",
        "start": 215.101,
        "duration": 2.536
    },
    {
        "text": "This sphere is surrounded by",
        "start": 217.637,
        "duration": 1.631
    },
    {
        "text": "a shell of energy that devours everything",
        "start": 219.268,
        "duration": 1.95
    },
    {
        "text": "it comes into contact with.",
        "start": 221.218,
        "duration": 1.562
    },
    {
        "text": "Whatever it touches",
        "start": 222.78,
        "duration": 2.059
    },
    {
        "text": "is eliminated for existence.",
        "start": 224.839,
        "duration": 2.152
    },
    {
        "text": "The bubble will continue to grow forever.",
        "start": 226.991,
        "duration": 2.407
    },
    {
        "text": "deleting the universe on its way.",
        "start": 229.398,
        "duration": 2.039
    },
    {
        "text": "There is no way to be warned,",
        "start": 231.437,
        "duration": 1.983
    },
    {
        "text": "since it's so fast.",
        "start": 233.42,
        "duration": 1.889
    },
    {
        "text": "But there's nothing we can do anyway.",
        "start": 235.309,
        "duration": 1.97
    },
    {
        "text": "Our destruction would be instant,",
        "start": 237.279,
        "duration": 2.09
    },
    {
        "text": "in a fraction of second,",
        "start": 239.369,
        "duration": 1.58
    },
    {
        "text": "Earth would be gone.",
        "start": 240.949,
        "duration": 2.27
    },
    {
        "text": "But it actually gets worse.",
        "start": 243.219,
        "duration": 1.741
    },
    {
        "text": "If the energy level",
        "start": 244.96,
        "duration": 2.727
    },
    {
        "text": "of the Higgs Field changes,",
        "start": 247.687,
        "duration": 1.35
    },
    {
        "text": "it changes all of physics.",
        "start": 249.037,
        "duration": 1.545
    },
    {
        "text": "In the true vacuum of the sphere,",
        "start": 250.582,
        "duration": 2.177
    },
    {
        "text": "the standard model will be overthrown,",
        "start": 252.759,
        "duration": 1.958
    },
    {
        "text": "superseded by different physics",
        "start": 254.717,
        "duration": 1.913
    },
    {
        "text": "that we don't know -",
        "start": 256.63,
        "duration": 1.51
    },
    {
        "text": "how fundamental particles behave,",
        "start": 258.14,
        "duration": 2.549
    },
    {
        "text": "how atoms hold together,",
        "start": 260.689,
        "duration": 1.649
    },
    {
        "text": "how chemicals react.",
        "start": 262.338,
        "duration": 2.274
    },
    {
        "text": "Vacuum decay won't just destroy life,",
        "start": 264.612,
        "duration": 2.739
    },
    {
        "text": "it will destroy chemistry itself,",
        "start": 267.351,
        "duration": 2.071
    },
    {
        "text": "making life as we know it impossible.",
        "start": 269.422,
        "duration": 2.528
    },
    {
        "text": "We simply have no idea",
        "start": 271.95,
        "duration": 1.901
    },
    {
        "text": "what it would be like inside.",
        "start": 273.851,
        "duration": 1.688
    },
    {
        "text": "It might be a shadow of what it is now,",
        "start": 275.539,
        "duration": 1.661
    },
    {
        "text": "or not.",
        "start": 277.2,
        "duration": 1.693
    },
    {
        "text": "We don't know.",
        "start": 278.893,
        "duration": 1.378
    },
    {
        "text": "If vacuum decay happens,",
        "start": 280.271,
        "duration": 1.808
    },
    {
        "text": "the outlook is indeed grim.",
        "start": 282.079,
        "duration": 2.613
    },
    {
        "text": "If you feel slightly worried now,",
        "start": 284.692,
        "duration": 1.628
    },
    {
        "text": "don't be.",
        "start": 286.32,
        "duration": 0.881
    },
    {
        "text": "At this point, false vacuum is speculation",
        "start": 287.201,
        "duration": 1.828
    },
    {
        "text": "based on our current understanding of",
        "start": 289.029,
        "duration": 1.39
    },
    {
        "text": "particle physics, which might be wrong.",
        "start": 290.419,
        "duration": 2.593
    },
    {
        "text": "It's kind of like using a ruler",
        "start": 293.012,
        "duration": 2.046
    },
    {
        "text": "to measure a continent.",
        "start": 295.058,
        "duration": 1.491
    },
    {
        "text": "(playful music)",
        "start": 296.549,
        "duration": 2.163
    },
    {
        "text": "Sure, you can do it, but you might be off",
        "start": 298.712,
        "duration": 2.297
    },
    {
        "text": "by quite a bit at the end.",
        "start": 301.009,
        "duration": 1.502
    },
    {
        "text": "Right now, no-one can say a vacuum decay",
        "start": 302.511,
        "duration": 3.259
    },
    {
        "text": "is a thing that's real",
        "start": 305.77,
        "duration": 1.231
    },
    {
        "text": "or just a scary idea.",
        "start": 307.001,
        "duration": 1.943
    },
    {
        "text": "But even if one or multiple spheres",
        "start": 308.944,
        "duration": 2.557
    },
    {
        "text": "of death have already started expanding,",
        "start": 311.501,
        "duration": 1.81
    },
    {
        "text": "the universe is so big",
        "start": 313.311,
        "duration": 1.248
    },
    {
        "text": "that they might not reach us",
        "start": 314.559,
        "duration": 1.644
    },
    {
        "text": "for billions of years.",
        "start": 316.203,
        "duration": 1.585
    },
    {
        "text": "If they're far enough away,",
        "start": 317.788,
        "duration": 1.326
    },
    {
        "text": "they might not ever be able to reach us",
        "start": 319.114,
        "duration": 1.579
    },
    {
        "text": "because of the expansion of the universe.",
        "start": 320.693,
        "duration": 2.359
    },
    {
        "text": "The speed of light is not that fast",
        "start": 323.052,
        "duration": 2.038
    },
    {
        "text": "on the scale of the universe.",
        "start": 325.09,
        "duration": 1.52
    },
    {
        "text": "So, while vacuum decay is",
        "start": 326.61,
        "duration": 2.551
    },
    {
        "text": "fascinatingly scary,",
        "start": 329.161,
        "duration": 1.099
    },
    {
        "text": "right now, there are other things",
        "start": 330.26,
        "duration": 1.46
    },
    {
        "text": "we should be more afraid of.",
        "start": 331.72,
        "duration": 1.944
    },
    {
        "text": "In contrast to vacuum decay,",
        "start": 333.664,
        "duration": 1.951
    },
    {
        "text": "we have the power to prepare",
        "start": 335.615,
        "duration": 1.615
    },
    {
        "text": "for most of them.",
        "start": 337.23,
        "duration": 3.55
    },
    {
        "text": "Videos like this one",
        "start": 340.78,
        "duration": 1.574
    },
    {
        "text": "take hundreds of hours to make, so",
        "start": 342.354,
        "duration": 1.727
    },
    {
        "text": "support us on Patreon",
        "start": 344.081,
        "duration": 1.351
    },
    {
        "text": "if you'd like to learn more about",
        "start": 345.432,
        "duration": 1.253
    },
    {
        "text": "the destruction of everything.",
        "start": 346.685,
        "duration": 1.597
    },
    {
        "text": "It really helps us out.",
        "start": 348.282,
        "duration": 1.512
    },
    {
        "text": "We tried to destroy the universe",
        "start": 349.794,
        "duration": 1.918
    },
    {
        "text": "at least once every few months.",
        "start": 351.712,
        "duration": 1.55
    },
    {
        "text": "So let us know in the comments,",
        "start": 353.262,
        "duration": 1.259
    },
    {
        "text": "if you have doomsday scenarios",
        "start": 354.521,
        "duration": 1.74
    },
    {
        "text": "you would like us to cover.",
        "start": 356.261,
        "duration": 1.923
    },
    {
        "text": "Subtitles by the Amara.org community",
        "start": 358.184,
        "duration": 0.816
    }
]